planDecision.template:
{systemPrompt}

# Current Workspace Files (non-exhaustive)
{projectFileStructure}

### IMPORTANT
Do not make assumptions about the main function of this workspace without inspecting the contents of its principal files first.

# User Request
{userPrompt}

# Junior Assistant
A junior assistant thought to run the following tool for you.
{planDecisionAssistant}

Based on both the list of Current Workspace Files and the junior assistant tool results above, you have two options:

1. If you have enough information to provide a complete answer, respond directly to the user.

2. If you need additional information to provide better assistance, create a plan in JSON format:

{
  "main_objective": "Concise description of the overall goal",
  "conclusion_from_junior_assistant_data": "An account of your findings based on the junior assistant data and any information that may be needed for completing the next steps in your plan",
  "junior_assistant_data_was_helpful": true,
  "next_step": {
    "objective": "What this step will accomplish",
    "tool": "tool_name",
    "prompt": "Precise and concise instructions for the tool (write as a sentence, not as final arguments). Must contain all details necessary to execute the tool without knowledge beyond the provided list of current workspace files and should not be vague in any way."
  },
  "later_steps": [
    "Step 2 objective (once next_step objective is complete)",
    "Step 3 objective"
  ]
}

# Available Tools
{toolNamesAndHints}

If the user prompt requires broad knowledge of the codebase, start by reading the README file if there is one. Do not search for files that are already listed in the Current Workspace Files, inspect them straight away.

IMPORTANT: Respond with raw JSON only. Do NOT wrap the JSON in markdown code blocks or backticks.

Set junior_assistant_data_was_helpful to true only if the tool results provided new information not already provided that helped towards answering the user's question otherwise set it to false.

Response:

planIteration.template:
{systemPrompt}

# Current Workspace Files (non-exhaustive)
{projectFileStructure}

# User Request
{userPrompt}

# Your Plan

## Main Objective
{objective}

## Completed Steps
{completedSteps}

## Current Step
{currentStep}

## Later Steps:
{nextSteps}

# Available Tools
{toolNamesAndHints}

# Your Response

Note: it is better to iterate on the same Step Objective until it is fully realized than to move onto a new objective without finishing the last. Please consider all previous conclusions listed in the Current and Previous Steps above before choosing your response option and avoid repetition at all cost like reviewing the same files from previous steps. ## Option A

If you have not fully reached your Current Step Objective (not Main Objective) but are confident you can get closer to it by executing more tools, reply with the following JSON ONLY, replacing the values with your own:

{
"continue_with_current_step": {
"notes_to_future_self": "An account of what you have learnt from the Completed Junior Assistant Task without reiterate any notes from before.",
"tool": "the tool_name for tool you will next use",
"prompt": "Clear instructions saying what you will do with this tool (write as a sentence, not as final arguments). This prompt must contain all details necessary to execute the tool without knowledge beyond the provided list of current workspace files and should not be vague in any way. If you are iterating over a file or search, ensure to provide that starting points and lengths where applicable."
}
}

## Option B

If you no longer want to work on the same objective and you know what your next objective should be, reply with the following JSON ONLY, replacing the values with your own:

{
"wrap_up_current_step": {
"notes_to_future_self": "An account of what you have learnt from the Completed Junior Assistant Task without reiterate any notes from before.",
"completed": true,
"success": true
},
"new_step": {
"objective": "your new step objective ",
"tool": "The tool_name for tool you are next going to use.",
"prompt": "Clear instructions saying what you will do with this tool (write as a sentence, not as final arguments). This prompt must contain all details necessary to execute the tool without knowledge beyond the provided list of current workspace files and should not be vague in any way."
},
// Optional: "later_steps": ["Updated step objective descriptions"] - only include if you want to change your current plans
}

NOTE: set "success" to false if the current step objective has not been fully realize and do not repeat the same objective or tool prompts from your Current Step, they must be different.

## Option C

If you have complete your previous objectives and are ready to conclude, provide a comprehensive, final conclusion that addresses the user request. Summarize key findings, and provide a complete answer to the original request. If you did not completely reach your Main Objective, say why. Provide your final answer or conclusion as text.

## IMPORTANT

If option A or B applies to you, reply with valid JSON structured exactly as specified, do not wrap the JSON in markdown code blocks or backticks and DO NOT MENTION WHICH OPTION YOU CHOSE OR ADD ANY OTHER TEXT, your response must only contain valid JSON.

If choosing option C, do not mention Option C, simply replay with text as specified.

Response:

